132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1334
H.P. 869 House of Representatives, March 27, 2025
An Act to Require Retailers to Place Any Liquor That Is Accessible
to Customers at Least 48 Inches from the Payment Terminal
Reference to the Committee on Veterans and Legal Affairs suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative BISHOP of Bucksport.
Cosponsored by Representatives: FAULKINGHAM of Winter Harbor, MCINTYRE of
Lowell, SIMMONS of Waldoboro, WHITE of Ellsworth.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 28-A MRSA §16 is enacted to read:
3 §16. Display of liquor
4 A retailer shall display liquor that is not placed in a display case or behind the counter
5 at least 48 inches from a cash register or payment terminal. For purposes of this section,
6 "payment terminal" means a device that facilitates the payment for a product by a retail
7 customer.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill requires a liquor retailer to display liquor that is not placed in a display case
1100 or behind the counter at least 48 inches from a cash register or payment terminal.
